Tommy, our little 12 lb love bug, just had surgery for his leg and hip last week. He is doing well however Tommy's recovery will take a number of weeks. He truly needs lots of TLC and attention. Tommy also has seizures and gets his meds twice a day to control them.

Tommy's wonderful foster mom has an emergency situation that is taking her out of town on Thursday. We need to find a loving foster home for Tommy very quickly-- and hope that we can can keep him there until he is recovered and can be adopted.

Please help us to help Tommy.

Today‚Äôs happy tail adoption story comes from Lilly who adopted two adorable cats, Fritz and Gracie, in May 2017. üòª

Lilly writes ‚ÄúI found out about North Central just by doing some research online. I absolutely fell in love with Fritz (the white/ginger boy) when I saw him. We both really perked up when we saw each other through the glass and cage. He basically jumped into my arms when I picked him up, so I knew he had to be mine. He was located in the adult cat room, even though he was only about 4 months old. Gracie was in the kitten room and I thought she was so beautiful. After hanging out in the kitten room, she got used to me and started reaching out for me to acknowledge her. I had my heart set on her, so the next day I came back with my mom and we were placed in a bidding war against other people who wanted Fritz and Gracie. I got them as my birthday gift. It was the best decision I‚Äôve ever made. They make me so happy and I talk about them to everyone. I‚Äôm such a proud cat lady. They‚Äôre very happy together and they make my life so much better than it would be.
When they were first put together, they couldn‚Äôt stand each other. They were fighting (and not in a loving way). I was super scared that they wouldn‚Äôt get along or that I‚Äôd have to choose one over the other, but they worked out their differences and now they‚Äôre inseparable!‚Äù
Thank you Lilly for adopting! We're so glad to hear Fritz and Gracie are getting along beautifully. üíû

AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION!!! Meet Brady, a Chocolate lab mix puppy born around late October, 2017. Brady came to Carolina Paws from a hoarding situation. When we first met him, he was too frightened to even move around in his crate and has scars on his cute face. We can only guess at the conditions he had to live in.His foster Mom says he is loving life to the fullest now! He is so excited to run around the house, discover toys, and to play with all of his foster brothers and sisters. Tug of war is a favorite game to play with the big dogs. But his most favorite thing to do is to receive love from his foster family. Brady can't get enough hugs and kisses. He currently weighs 10 pounds and should weigh around 50 to 60 pounds when full grown. He is treat motivated and is eager to please. Brady would be best suited in a home and not an apartment and will need a structurally fenced in backyard to run and play in. Due to his very young age, he will need a home were someone is home more often than not and with children that are 8 years of age or older. He can seem a little shy at first when meeting new dogs and people, but he gets over it quickly and then is ready to play. Brady's adoption fee includes his current vetting, and his future neuter, rabies and microchip. If you are looking for an awesome family dog, or a best friend, Brady is your guy.
